The paper deals with object localization using convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves adding an additional module to classification networks, which is a technique used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of background images to extract foreground object proposals, which could fall under multimedia (cs.MM) or information retrieval (cs.IR) categories.
